parameters.definition: Maximum number of wired headphones that can be produced per day by the wired team
Maximum number of wireless headphones that can be produced per day by the wireless team
Maximum capacity of shared audio testing machine per day

description: A audio company make two types of headphones: wired headphones and wireless headphones. Two different teams make each type of headphones. The wired team can make at most \param{MaxWired} wired headphones per day and the wireless team can make at most \param{MaxWireless} wireless headphones per day. Both teams require use of a shared audio testing machine, and this machine can be used to make a maximum of \param{MaxTesting} headphones per day. The profit per wired headphone is \param{ProfitWired} and the profit per wireless headphone \param{ProfitWireless}. How many of each headphone should be made to maximize profit?
